  "experimental_conditions": {
    "001": {
      "0": {
        "detector": [
          {
            "x4_code": "(MAGSP,SISD)",
            "free_txt": [
              " Reaction products recoiled to the",
              "Berkeley Gas-filled Separator, where they were",
              "separated according to ions A/q. At the BGS focal",
              "plane ions can be implanted into a retractable 32 x",
              "32 double-sided silicon strip detector or ions could",
              "pass through 2.1 mu-m thick Ti foil into FIONA setup."
            ]
          },
          {
            "x4_code": "(SISD)",
            "free_txt": [
              " After magnetic analysis in BGS, the beam",
              "entered the FIONA setup, which consisted of beam",
              "manipulation elements as RFQ cooler and trap,",
              "accelerating element with focusing, steering and",
              "diagnostic. The accelerated beam entered",
              "low-background area where the ions were separated by",
              "their A/q in a trochoidal spectrometer which utilizes",
              "crossed magnetic and electric fields, tuned to force",
              "the ions traveling through the spectrometer to take",
              "trochoidal trajectories. At the FIONA focal plane",
              "ions are implanted into 32 x 32 strip double sided Si",
              "strip detector."
            ]
          }
        ],
        "facility": [
          {
            "x4_code": "(CYCLO,1USABRK)",
            "free_txt": [
              " Experiment performed at the 88-inch",
              "cyclotron at the Lawrence Berkeley National Laboratory"
            ]
          }
        ],
        "method": [
          {
            "x4_code": "(ACTIV)",
            "free_txt": [
              " Evaporation residue (EVR)-alpha-alpha",
              "correlations were searched for in data taken at the",
              "220 MeV beam energy with the BGS focal plane detector",
              "inserted and FIONE focal plane detector. Time windows",
              "were expanded up to 30 and 300 s for EVR-alpha1 and",
              "EVR-alpha1-alpha2, respectively. The 244Md was",
              "identified according to EVR mass and energies of",
              "series of decay alphas."
            ]
          }
        ],
        "sample": [
          {
            "x4_code": null,
            "free_txt": [
              "The beam was incident on a 4\"-diameter target wheel",
              "rotating at approx. 30 Hz, located upstream of the BGS.",
              "The target wheel contained four target segments - three",
              "segments of 209Bi with an average thickness of",
              "0.500 mg/cm2 for  the production of Md isotopes and",
              "a fourth segment  made of 165Ho with an average",
              "thickness of 0.365 mg/cm2 for the production of At",
              "isotopes."
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    },
